            <h3 class="fontWeight400">Research Activities</h3>
            <ul class="listCircle">
              <li>Reviewed current provider workflows</li>
              <li>Tested existing notification/message systems directly</li>
              <li>Interviewed active QPs</li>
              <li>Mapped communication flows and operational behaviors</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>


      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h3 class="fontWeight400">Key Behavioral Findings</h3>
            <h5 class="fontWeight400 greyBg400 greyBg200 border-radius paddingXS">💡 Reservation is the primary object. Communication is secondary.</h5>

            <h5>QPs organize work around:</h5>
            <ul class="listCircle">
              <li>Delivery timing</li>
              <li>Reservation stages</li>
              <li>Operational urgency</li>
              <li>Logistics coordination</li>
            </ul>
            <h5>They did not organize work around standalone message threads.</h5>

          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h3 class="fontWeight400">QPs built external operational systems</h3>

            <h5>Providers relied on:</h5>
            <ul class="listCircle">
              <li>Gmail</li>
              <li>Texting</li>
              <li>Google Keep templates</li>
              <li>Manual scheduling</li>
              <li>Personal workflow systems</li>
            </ul>
            <h5>They used these tools to compensate for fragmented platform coordination tools.</h5>

          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h3 class="fontWeight400">Messaging itself was not the core problem</h3>
            <h5>Email-based communication already supported many existing workflows successfully.</h5>
            <div class="spacingSmall"></div>
            <h5>The larger issue was:</h5>
            <ul class="listCircle">
              <li>Operational fragmentation</li>
              <li>Notification overload</li>
              <li>Poor urgency hierarchy</li>
              <li>Weak reservation-centered coordination</li>
            </ul>
            <h5>These issues made reservation coordination harder to manage.</h5>

          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h5 class="fontWeight400 greyBg400 greyBg200 border-radius paddingXS">💡 Key insight: Providers were not struggling because they lacked another messaging channel. They were struggling because communication was disconnected from the reservation work it supported.</h5>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>

  </section>

